## Estrutura de diretórios do Backend

apps/api/src/

- domain/
  - entitities/ # Entidades de domínio
  - errors/ # Erros de domínio
  - repositories/ # Interface de repositórios
- infrastructure/
  - database/ # Prisma-client
  - providers/ # Stripe, OpenAI, Email
- interface
  - http/
    - controllers/ # Fastify route handlers
    - middlewares/ # Auth, RBAC, rate-limit
    - routes/ # Registro de rotas
    - schemas/ # Schemas
- shared/ - errors/ # AppError, HttpException - decorators/ # Utilitários
  server.ts
  app.ts

## Fastify

- Utilize plugins
- Separe rotas de controllers
- Utilize hooks para auth e tenant

## Banco de Dados

- PostgreSQL
- Prisma ORM
- Migrations obrigatórias
- Nunca usar SQL raw sem justificativa
- Criar schema.prisma com todos os modelos
- Configurar DATABASE_URL no .env
- Rodar: pnpm prisma migrate dev --name init
- Gerar client: pnpm prisma generate
- Seed inicial com dados de exemplo

## Validação

- Zod para:
  - request body
  - query params
  - env vars

## Auth (Better Auth)

- Instalar Better Auth: pnpm add better-auth;
- Configurar providers (Email, Google, GitHub);
- Implementar plugin RBAC do Better Auth
- Criar tabelas de sessao e token no schema Prisma
- Registrar rotas de auth no Fastify: /api/auth/\*
- Nunca confiar em dados vindos do client

## Packages Compartilhados

@m-move-app/types
Conteudo do package de tipos:

- IUser, IWorkoutPlan, IWorkoutDay, IWorkoutExercise
- IWorkoutSession, IPhysicalAssessment, IGym
- ISubscription, IAIChat, IAIChatMessage
- DTOs de request/response para cada endpoint
- Tipos de paginacao: PaginatedResponse<T>

@m-move-app/validators
Schemas Zod reutilizados no backend e frontend:

- createWorkoutPlanSchema, updateWorkoutPlanSchema
- createWorkoutDaySchema, createWorkoutExerciseSchema
- createPhysicalAssessmentSchema
- loginSchema, registerSchema
- generateWorkoutWithAISchema

@m-move-app/utils

- calculateStreak(sessions: WorkoutSession[], plan: WorkoutPlan): number
- calculateBMI(weight: number, height: number): number
- formatDuration(seconds: number): string
- getWeekDayFromDate(date: Date, timezone: string): WeekDay

## Padrões

- Controllers não possuem regra de negócio
- Services concentram a lógica
- Repositories apenas acessam dados
- Seguir estritamente TDD. Para cada endpoint:
  1. Escrever testes com Vitest + Supertest,
  2. Implementar o minimo para passar,
  3. Refatorar.

## Rotas da API

- Auth -> /api/auth -> POST /register, POST /login, POST /logout, GET /me, POST /refresh

- Users -> /api/users -> GET /, GET /:id, PATCH /:id, DELETE /:id

- Workout Plans -> /api/workout-plans -> GET /, POST /, GET /:id, PATCH /:id, DELETE /:id, POST /:id/activate

- Workout Days -> /api/workout-plans/:id/days -> GET /, POST /, PATCH /:dayId, DELETE /:dayId

- Exercises -> /api/workout-days/:id/exercises -> GET /, POST /, PATCH /:exId, DELETE /:exId, PATCH /reorder

- Sessions -> /api/sessions -> POST /start, PATCH /:id/complete, GET /history, GET /streak

- Assessments -> /api/assessments -> GET /, POST /, GET /:id, GET /history/:userId

- Gym -> /api/gym -> POST /, GET /:id, PATCH /:id, POST /members, DELETE /members/:id

- AI -> /api/ai -> POST /chat, GET /chats, POST /generate-plan, GET /insights/:userId

- PT Invites -> /api/pt/invites -> POST / (enviar convite), GET / (listar convites), DELETE /:id (revogar), POST /accept (aluno aceita token)

- Subscriptions -> /api/subscriptions -> POST /checkout, POST /portal, GET /status, POST /webhook
